##Hangzhou launches "Resume Work Special Train" NATIONAL PICK-UP: Free Ride, get off the package

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

"manpower shortages are the most immediate and pervasive problem. "

At 18:15 p.m. on February 18, the D5580 train from Huangshan City North railway station in Anhui Province to Hangzhou East left on time. The 543 passengers on this "special train" for Hangzhou workers returning to work are all workers returning to Hangzhou, making them a "valuable resource" that Hangzhou companies are in urgent need of.

This is already the third special train to resume work in Hangzhou.

At 13:57 on February 16, the country's first custom-made train for the return of migrant workers departs from Guiyang North railway station. Nearly 300 migrant workers from Guizhou Province take the G4138 bullet train from Guiyang North Railway Station to Hangzhou. The second special train G4391 departed from Chengdu East railway station at 9:30 am on February 17 and was added for the return journey of Sichuan migrant workers.

Relevant staff of the Hangzhou Economic and information bureau told China News weekly that the current epidemic in Hangzhou is relatively stable, and the whole city is speeding up the resumption of work. The Economic and Information Bureau learned during a visit to enterprises that, "manpower shortages are the most immediate and pervasive problem. ".

In order to speed up the return journey of the staff, the special train for resuming work has been put on the schedule. Starting on February 16, free trains will be launched at the rate of one train a day in Hangzhou, from Guizhou, Sichuan and Anhui provinces, where Hangzhou has a high concentration of workers.

"Free Shipping" mode

From Huangshan City North Railway Station to Hangzhou East Railway Station, the high-speed railway usually takes only 1 hour and 52 minutes. Recently, however, due to the impact of the COVID-19 epidemic, part of the country's train outage, many areas closed village, road closure, closure area to fight the epidemic. The virus was sniping at the same time, the staff difficult to return, the enterprise difficult to start work.

Hangzhou had also issued many special policies to support the resumption of work. On February 12th, for example, Hangzhou announced 12 policies to reduce financing costs, waive guarantee fees and reduce rent for businesses. While gaining substantial benefits, enterprises are faced with the embarrassing situation of no one to work.

The Hangzhou operation, mainly by the Hangzhou Economic and Social Commission and the Hangzhou Municipal Bureau of two departments to be responsible. The economic and Credit Commission of Hangzhou told China News Week that the economic and credit commission has the closest ties with enterprises. How many employees do enterprises hope to have on the job these days and report their needs, "after we put it all together, we lined up a row of reworkers, which had the most concentrated travel time, and finally we decided to open the special train, Guiyang 16. "

The reason for choosing these areas, because the home of Hangzhou's enterprise employees are relatively concentrated in Guizhou, Sichuan and several other regions. In addition, for example, Qiandongnan Prefecture of Guizhou is also an area with Hangzhou's counterpart support. The Qiandongnan Prefecture People's Social Bureau has done a lot of work in cooperation with Hangzhou. The Qiandongnan Prefecture People's Social Bureau has sent information about the workers who have returned to work on special trains to the People's Social Bureau of each district and county, provision of pick-up service for returning workers.

For the Economic and Information Commission of Hangzhou, this is a huge task. In order to coordinate the travel plans of these people, they need to call one by one, inform the migrant workers, give the train information, and ask if they can not catch the special train, "Most of them are in the surrounding districts and counties. It takes time to get to the station. The final statistics are those who can arrive on time and meet the requirements for epidemic prevention. "

Only five staff members from the Hangzhou Economic and Information Commission were in charge of the operation, while nearly 300 people were on the first special train to resume work, but the actual number of people calling to inform the authorities far exceeded this number, "The actual number of contacts was about 1,200, and a lot of people couldn't come. "

"It's actually a stupid way of doing things that we have no choice but to do, " said a staff member of the Hangzhou Economic and Credit Commission. However, some enterprises that use a large number of workers have started to directly link up with information about migrant workers and then feed it back to the economic and Credit Commission, "It takes a little bit of the pressure off our work. "

The special train for the resumption of work, the Hangzhou Municipal Government Unified Coordination and bear the cost, ride on the resumption of work special train personnel transport costs free.

From the car to get off, these workers can also enjoy the whole "customized service. ". After arriving at the station on time, migrant workers from all over Guizhou will be able to enter the station with their ID cards. Staff at the Shanghai Railway Bureau told China News weekly that the train would stop briefly at some stations from its starting point to its final destination, but would not pick up or drop off passengers. When the train arrives at the station, Hangzhou Municipal Bureau of Social Affairs and the departments of social affairs in all districts will arrive at the station to greet it. At the high-speed train station, the passengers also received a treat -- a bag containing food such as bread, milk and face masks.

The resumption of the train is mainly aimed at two aspects of personnel: First, the Enterprise's original pre-festival workers, second, the enterprise in the field of new recruits. Staff travelling on the special train must hold Hangzhou Health Green Code, and there is no fever, cough, shortness of breath and other suspected symptoms of new pneumonia. Moreover, the application for special train back to Hangzhou enterprises, must be able to properly solve the problem of staff accommodation.

The health code is the first health assessment certificate based on digital capability introduced in Hangzhou, which can be used as a passport for workers returning to work during the epidemic. On February 11, Hangzhou City took the lead in the implementation of the Green Code by the code, the Red Code and Yellow Code of the personnel should be isolated according to regulations and Healthy Punch card, after meeting the conditions will be converted to Green Code.

Special train approval has been reduced from 15 days to 20 hours

On February 15, at a press conference organized by the Joint Defense and Control Mechanism of the State Council, Li Wenxin, deputy general manager of the State Railway Group, said that originally the railway passenger flow was expected to be 280 million after the Spring Festival, starting from February 11, the railway has sent fewer than 1 million passengers four days in a row, with 115 million refunds.

In order to solve the problem of returning to work, China Railway Group put forward the opinion of opening special train publicly for the first time. "Our current capacity is 8 million a day. With a 50 percent occupancy rate, we can meet at least 4 million daily passenger trips, " Li said. "The current demand for passenger trips is less than 1 million. We can also organize special trains or charters to ensure an orderly return journey from peak to peak for groups of migrant workers with relatively concentrated input and output. "

"Our railway company has the capacity, as long as the other side has this demand, we can cooperate to do this, " a staff member at the Hangzhou Station of the Shanghai Branch told China News Weekly. The government reports back to us on the demand and then informs and arranges for the returning workers, which requires information to flow in both directions."

The above-mentioned personnel, in normal terms, Spring Festival and other holidays to add the train, must be declared 15 days in advance. Now, the whole process is compressed to less than 20 hours. From Hangzhou to Guizhou, Sichuan, and then to the railway sector, efficient operation of all sides, promoting the country's first special train to resume work.

In order to avoid the risk of the spread of the epidemic to the greatest extent possible, under the overall coordination of the China National Railway Group, the special train arrangement for returning workers in Hangzhou was drawn up jointly with the Shanghai and Chengdu Railway Administration of China, we will improve measures for the prevention and control of epidemics and passenger transport services in areas such as passenger arrival, waiting, boarding and departure.

At the Guiyang North Railway Station, special green channels have been set up to guide migrant workers to the station, more than 30 people have been assigned 12 sets of equipment to enhance temperature checks, and special waiting areas have been set up for migrant workers to sit separately.

At present, Suzhou is also closely following Hangzhou, ready to join the ranks of the special train to resume work. The first batch of special trains will set the direction of Lu'an and Shangqiu, and the next batch of special trains to resume work will be adjusted according to the needs of enterprises.

However, a staff member from the Hangzhou Municipal Bureau of people and Social Affairs also told China News Weekly: "The work of the special train for resuming work is relatively huge and complicated, and the specific operation mode may change in the future. "

From all over the world

It is an urgent task for many places to prevent and control the epidemic at one hand and resume work and production at the other.

Li Tie, chief economist of the Center for Urban and small town reform and development, said in a recent post: "It is recommended that officials at all levels of government should have a sense of risk-taking and maximize the ways and means to improve scientific prevention and control. Only when the fear of the cadres is lowered, can the excessive panic in the society be alleviated. We hope that in cities where the outbreak is not serious and has already achieved full control results, we can resume work, open business and resume normal economic and social life in a timely manner while improving the capacity and means for prevention and control."

In addition to Hangzhou, Zhejiang has issued a lot of "big gift bags" for returning workers, using special planes, special trains, special buses and other ways to transport returning workers.

Jiashan picked up hundreds of Sichuan employees on charter flights, and all employees who returned to their posts were given free rides, two-thirds of the cost being borne by the Jiashan County government and one-third by their companies.

Herning instructs companies to charter cars, planes and trains, to take new and old employees back to work, and the government to pay two thirds of the cost of the journey. For key areas, key enterprises employees, by the government organized special train, special train, special carriage responsible for pick-up, all expenses paid by the government.

In Huzhou, no less than 100 million yuan in incentive funds for enterprises to resume work and production are earmarked for enterprises to resume work and production, and 1,000 yuan in one-off living subsidies for new employees. If the Enterprise Unified Organization to outside the City Staff Charter return, charter fees by the full government subsidies.

Ningbo's practice is that the month after the outbreak of the disease lifted the number of enterprises participating in social insurance compared with the same period last year, for every one new person, according to the standard of 500 yuan per person subsidy enterprises, each enterprise maximum total subsidy not exceeding 300,000 yuan.
